column5: hey guys, first thing i want to say is thanks guys for all the halp on quinte. We were on the water by 8am last sat >Ice guy and I were both pumped cause it was our first time fishong Quinte.we travelled to the reach and started trolling planners and dipsys.two hours of nothing and then Iceguys planner goes off in about 70 feet of water down about 40. And we knew it was a biggen right away. Ive never seen a walleye that big before wow.congrats Iceguy.we fished until dusk with only one pike caught by iceguy in 100 FOT. I got skunked but  ill be back .It was great weather and great company. Next time those walleye are in trouble....lol   lol ,,,,theres the report but how do i post the pic on this new site    Iceguy.....let me know if your free on FRI to hit cooks for some perch at 11am
can't wait to see the pic!!   Try this link  OFC Help
ill show you when i get home ... same as before ,.. very simple
Heres the PIG !!  11.4lb    heres the pic of the  pike he caought in 115 FOW    ...the crazy ehh....lol
nice report & pics,wat to go guys, you will get em,next time
Looks like both the walleye and pike are feeding well.  Congrats on the productive outing.
That walleye is seriously putting on the feed, wtg.  Mike
nice fish iceguy! you'll have to show us how you do it! im planning on heading out this sunday morning, City, Snagmaster you in?
you didnt even invite me ...  Ill be in niagara... no quinte for me
NICE!!   Gotta love those well fed fish!
Thanks Snagmaster for postin the report, Had an awsome time, think we can get out  one more time Quinte or the Niagara bar?
ya hopefully the weather is ok
That's one seriously nice looking hog you got there!! Great job....and a memorable first time at BOQ!
Great pic of that eye w/ her fins out and dorsal up!
